On Wednesday, January 13, the Federal Government will shut down Lagos Island-bound traffic on the Third Mainland Bridge for two weeks.
 
This is part of the ongoing rehabilitation being carried out on the longest bridge in West Africa.The Federal Controller, Works Lagos, Popoola Olukayode, announced this in a statement at the weekend, entitled: ‘Shifting of current diversion point towards Oworosonki and closing of the Lagos Island-bound carriageway, including the Adekunle slip Road.’  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .